{"word":"κατόμνυμι","slug":"κατόμνυμι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κατόμνυμι</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-ομοῦμαι</el>) (aor1 <el>-ώμοσα</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to confirm by oath</i>, <el>τί τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to swear that . .</i> , <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to call to witness, swear by</i>, <el>τὴν ἐμὴν ψυχήν</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> also, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>to take an oath against, accuse on oath</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}